page.title: 10Winster Area
page.content: The whole territory is varied, from 150-600 ft above sea level; the roads and lanes have steep descents with many turns, and every vista gives views of the valleys with streams, craggy tops and bog patches. The white and grey slated houses stand out to view surrounded by trees and many lovely gardens full of coulour in sun or shade. Compston House on the main road near the village hall was the old post office and is a very typical lakeland house with deep porch surrounding slate dry walls, and the characteristic hydrangea bushes. Cat Crag at 610 ft and next view point at 510 ft is the Ordanance Survey beacon is still in use.
